The paper discusses diffractive optical neural networks for machine learning, specifically for object classification and imaging. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also discusses improvements in accuracy, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of optical systems also relates to robotics (cs.RO) and signal processing (cs.SD).
